content.description: The crux is the beginning. Good footwork will get you through with no prob.
content.location: Just to the right of the narly 10d.

content.description: The start is the hardest part of this. Smooth sailing from there on.
content.location: Shares the first bolt with Quatchatarium and Blank.

content.description:
Shares the starting bolt with 2 other routes, RIP and Blank. 

  The start is just a pop-up and most of the route is juggy. Really fun climb.
ok warmup for the holladay wall.
content.location: leftmost route on the wall, to the right of the small roof.  this route and opticalrectuminitus are the only routes on this section of the wall.

content.description:
if you cant reach the first bolt from the ground, stick clip it.  relatively easy climbing to the second bolt, i did not stick clip it like hogge recommends but it felt fine.   

  from austin climbing: 50' right of the quatch start under a low dihedral roof pull a long left pointing edge.  runout to bolt 2; we recommend stick clipping it.  primo face moves.
content.location: 50' right of the quatch; the only other bolted route on this section of holladay wall.

content.description: Low crux, this route follows long moves on big holds, trending up and right to finish to chains just left of those of Monfi.
content.location: Starts left of the steep, large, arete roof on the Holliday wall.

content.description: A nice warm up for the grade. Start where just about every other route starts on this wall and move up and to the left along a line of permas. Fight the pump.
Pretty straigh forward. Get on the ledge, get your first clip in, and climb up...crux is at start and then eases to 5.5/5.6 climbing to anchors.

Starts the same as The Mexican, however, at bolt 2 (a permadraw), start traversing right on the ledge and follow permadraws to the anchors above the start of the Awesome Roof Wall. Be aware of bees near the anchors. If bees start attacking, just lower on permadraw.
content.protection: 1 bolt, 5 permadraws, anchors. Also, ***BE ALERT*** Under the anchors, there's a small cave with a beehive the size of a basketball. They can get aggressive when disturbed.
content.location: Same start as The Mexican. Wall/route is just left of the awesome roof wall.

content.description:
Although the rock on this route isnt the best it has some fun interesting movement.  

  Straight forward long lock-offs and pulls on crimps lead you to the lip of a mini roof where you move to a sinker 3 finger pocket. Don't celebrate yet though because there is another very long pull up to a jug which leads to easier climbing.
content.protection: 6 bolts, 1 is a directional which is best to be extended
content.location: Line right of Ode to an Era on Holiday wall

content.description: Climbs the crack under the roof and out the left side.
content.location: Left most route on Holladay wall. 15 feet right of The Quatch.

content.description: The crux is definitely the beginning. Be strong and pull through. If you're short.... well good luck.
content.location: To the right of the 3 routes which share the same first bolt and in front of a skinny tree. It's hard to miss. The start has very high holds.
Start monfi, finish on anchors to the right of Monfi anchors. Solid jugs under anchors.

content.description: The first part is the hardest part. Just go up and to the right.
content.location: Shares the first bolt with 2 other routes, Quatchatarium and R.I.P.

content.description: Variation of 10 9 8 Direct. Start Monfi; bale early to 10 9 8 Direct's last bolt and anchors.
Look for the new shiny bolts. Don't get your feet wet.
content.location: Start in the dihedral on the ledge to the left of the Monfi/Quatch/RIP/Blank start.

content.description: Shady. Usually not crowded at all.
